    <h1>  <em> Curry pasta with ground beef recipe and pineaple</em></h1>
    
    <img src="ground beef and pasta with pineapple .jpeg"  
     a picture of a plate of pasta and groung beef
    style="width:600px;height:auto;">

    <p>This is a relatively easy recipe to follow and that anyone can 
        make at home in less than an hour to safisfy themselves. Serving 
        size and quantity is dependent on how many people are planning to eat.
    </p>
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>

    <ul>
        <li>2 tablespoons of olive oil</li>
        <li>1 pound of ground beef</li>
        <li>1 pound of pasta of your preference</li>
        <li>1(15 ounce) can pineaple chunks, drained,liquid reserved</li>
        <li>1 medium leek, cleaned and thinly sliced</li>
        <li>3 tablespoons of mild curry powder</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon instant vegetable bouillon granules</li>
        <li>salt and freshly ground pepper to taste</li>
        <li>1/2 cup of ketchup</li>
        <li>4 tablespoons of tomato paste</li>
        <li>1 cup heavy cream</li>
    </ul>

    <h3> Directions </h3>

    <ol>
        <li> First
            <p>prepare a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
                Add your pasta in for cooking once the water starts to boil.
                Stir occasionally until the pasta is cook but slightly firm.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li> Second
            <p> Meanwhile, heat oil in a large skillet. Add ground beef and cook,
                stirring until browned, about 5-10 minutes depending on the cooking level.
                Add drained pineapple chunks and leek and cook over medium to high heat
                for about 5 minutes. Pour in about 1/2 of the pineapple juice. Season with 
                curry powder, bouillon, salt and pepper.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li> Third
            <p> Stir in ketchup and tomato paste until it is well conbbined. Cover and simmer
                over low heat for 5-8 minutes. If the sauce seems dry, add more pineaple juice.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li> Fourth 
           <p>  Pour in cream and mix to combine. Cook for about 2-4 minutes </p>
         </li>
         <li> Fifth
            <p> Drain pasta and add the skillet with the sauce. Mix well and serve.</p>
         </li>
    

    </ol>
<div class="Elbows and ground beef">
    <h1> <em> Elbows and ground beef</em></h1>
    </div>

    <img src="Elbows and ground beef .webp"
    image of a plate of elbows and ground beef
    style="width:450px;height:autox;">


        <p> Elbow pasta with ground beef, bell pepper and onions with tomato sauce. 
        This is a quick and easy meal. Serve with a salad and loaf of bread, delicious !
    </p>

    <h2> Ingredients</h2>

    <ul>
        <li>1 onion chopped</li>
        <li>1 1/2 pound of lean ground beef</li>
        <li>1 green bell pepper, chopped</li>
        <li>2 (29 ounce) cans tomato sauce</li>
        <li>1 (16 ounce) package macaroni</li>
    </ul>

    <h3> Directions </h3>

    <ol>
        <li> First
            <p>Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain.</p>
        </li>
        <li> Second 
            <p>In a Dutch oven, brown ground beef over medium heat.Add chopped
                onion, and cook until onion is soft. Add green pepper and tomato 
                sauce; cook until pepper is soft. 
            </p>
        </li>
        <li> Third</li>
        <p>Serve sauce over pasta</p>
    </ol>
    

    <h1> <em>Ground Beef Yorkshire</em></h1>

    <!--this is an example of a HTML commnent -->

    <img src="Ground Beef Yorkshire .webp"
    a plate of sliced ground beef yorkshire
    style="width:450px;height:autopx;">

    <p>This dish features ground beef and Yorkshire pudding in a comfort food one 
        dish casserole.
    </p>

    <h2> Ingredients</h2>

    <ul>
        <li>1 cup of all purpose flour</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon of baking powder</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon of salt</li>
        <li>3 eggs, beaten</li>
        <li>1 1/2 cup of milk</li>
        <li>1/4 cup of melted butter</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon of dried parsley</li>
        <li>1 pound of ground beef extra lean</li>
        <li>1/4 cup of finely chopped onions</li>
        <li>1/4 cup of diced celery</li>
        <li>1/4 cup of chopped carrot</li>
        <li>1/2 teaspoon of salt</li>
        <li>1/4 teaspoon of pepper</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon of Worcestershire sauce</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon of steak sauce (such as A.1.)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Directions</h3>

    <ol>
        <li> First
            <p>Preheat an oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease an 
                8x8 inch baking dish.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li> Second 
            <p> Whisk together the flour, the baking powder, and the 1 tablespoon 
                of salt. In a separate bowl, whisk together the egg mixture over the 
                flour mixture; beat until well blended. Stir in parsley; set aside.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li> Third
            <p> Heat a large skillet over medium high heat and stir in the ground 
                beef and onion. Cook and stir until the beef is crumbly, evenly
                browned, and no longer pink, about 10 minutes. Drain and disgard any 
                excess grease. 
            </p>
        </li>
        <li> Fourth 
            <p> Combine the drained meat mixture with celery, carrot, the 1/2 teaspoon of
                salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, and steak sauce. Spread the meat mixture
                evenly into the prepared baking dish. Pour the batter over the meat.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li> Fifth
            <p>Bake in the preheated oven until the pudding has risen tall and is golden,
                 for about 45 minutes. Serve immediately
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>

